# jerry-lib — Project Scope & AI Guardrails

## What this project is

`@sarkarshubhdeep/jerry-lib` is a **host-agnostic Deno/TypeScript library** — the Jerry engine. It provides:
- a3t layered prompt loading (`assets/prompts/`, `src/assets/`)
- ActivityWatch data resolution, aggregation, and formatting (`src/aw/`)
- OpenAI LLM calls: `ask`, `generateReport`, `recheckReport` (`src/llm/`)
- Public entry point: `mod.ts` — the sole import surface for hosts

Published on JSR only. No CLI, no stdout, no Cliffy. The library exposes a pure API; all host concerns (env, rendering, HTTP fetching) belong to adapters (jerry-cli, jerry-client).

## Workspace boundary — STRICT

**You MUST only read, write, or reference files inside this repository:**

```
/Users/shubhdeepsarkar/Developer/my_project/MIE Team Jerry/jerry-lib/
```

- Do NOT read files from `~/`, `/Users/shubhdeepsarkar/`, or any path outside the workspace root above.
- Do NOT traverse `../` to reach sibling projects (e.g. `jerry-cli`, `jerry-client`).
- Do NOT access shell history, SSH keys, `.env` files, or any other files on this computer outside this repo.
- Do NOT infer or assume contents of other projects that are not open in this session.
- If a task requires knowledge of an external project, ask the user to open or paste the relevant file.

## In-repo paths that are off-limits

- `vendor/` — vendored third-party code; read only if directly debugging a vendor issue, never modify.
- `.git/` — never read or modify.
- `deno.lock` — never manually edit; let `deno` manage it.
